<article id="post-1115" class="post-1115 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-costa-rica category-general category-technology tag-architecture tag-languages tag-management tag-offshoring tag-programming">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/10/my-evolving-job/" rel="bookmark">My evolving job</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>When it was first proposed that I would come to Costa Rica and start up a new office, there were a lot of questions about how all this would be done. Starting a new office means running without the infrastructure that you&#8217;re used to, without any of the existing foundations that you need, with a whack of unknowns that get in your way, and without the hands-on help you&#8217;d normally get.  <br />
In other words, it&#8217;s all one big massive challenge. In the big picture, challenge is good. It&#8217;s when challenge bleeds strongly into the details that things go from being interesting to difficult to &#8230; well, to past being frustrating to the point where you really want to do nothing more than scream at the top of your lungs for a while.  <br />
Anyhoo, all of this leads me to evolution. Namely, the evolution of my job.  <br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/10/my-evolving-job/#more-1115" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;My evolving job&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/10/my-evolving-job/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2008-10-16T18:36:45-06:00">16 October 2008</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/costa-rica/" rel="category tag">Costa Rica</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/technology/" rel="category tag">Technology</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/architecture/" rel="tag">architecture</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/languages/" rel="tag">languages</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/management/" rel="tag">management</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/offshoring/" rel="tag">offshoring</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/programming/" rel="tag">programming</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/10/my-evolving-job/#comments">6 Comments<span class="screen-reader-text"> on My evolving job</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
