<article id="post-1030" class="post-1030 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-costa-rica category-general tag-mobile tag-phones">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/08/the-phones-i-ordered-finally-showed-up/" rel="bookmark">The phones I ordered finally showed up</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Augh.<br />
I called it yesterday, when I got my new cell phone. A month ago, we ordered phones over the internet. They were shipped US Postal Service. They entered Costa Rica on 8 July. And then sat in customs. When I got my Nokia, I said (knowing this was truth) that our eBay-ordered phones would show up today.<br />
I hate it when I&#8217;m right.</p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/08/the-phones-i-ordered-finally-showed-up/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2008-08-08T16:42:21-06:00">8 August 2008</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/costa-rica/" rel="category tag">Costa Rica</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/mobile/" rel="tag">mobile</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/phones/" rel="tag">phones</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/08/the-phones-i-ordered-finally-showed-up/#respond">Leave a comment<span class="screen-reader-text"> on The phones I ordered finally showed up</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
</article><!-- #post-1030 -->

<article id="post-1028" class="post-1028 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-costa-rica category-general category-technology tag-gsm tag-mobile tag-phones">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/08/my-new-1998-era-nokia-tdma-cell-phone/" rel="bookmark">My new 1998-era Nokia TDMA cell phone</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Note today&#8217;s date: 8 August 2008. That&#8217;s (almost) two months since we first came to Costa Rica. Two months ago, <a href="http://www.sowrey.org/2008/06/its-manana-time/">we tried to start getting things</a> like cars, bank accounts, work visas (a fairly significant need), and cell phones, as these were the things we felt were necessary to be able to do our jobs effectively.<br />
To date, we&#8217;ve all managed to get bank accounts. Only <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/sowrey/2723556436/">Mark has successfully bought a car</a> (Jason and Jen are still looking, and we&#8217;re <a href="http://twitter.com/sowrey/statuses/879475198">still waiting for our money to arrive from Canada</a>), and the work visas are in the application process (read: not completed).<br />
Yesterday, despite phones ordered via eBay still being stuck in Costa Rica customs, we finally got cell phones.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/08/my-new-1998-era-nokia-tdma-cell-phone/#more-1028" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;My new 1998-era Nokia TDMA cell phone&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/08/my-new-1998-era-nokia-tdma-cell-phone/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2008-08-08T09:18:22-06:00">8 August 2008</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/costa-rica/" rel="category tag">Costa Rica</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/technology/" rel="category tag">Technology</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/gsm/" rel="tag">gsm</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/mobile/" rel="tag">mobile</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/phones/" rel="tag">phones</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/08/my-new-1998-era-nokia-tdma-cell-phone/#respond">Leave a comment<span class="screen-reader-text"> on My new 1998-era Nokia TDMA cell phone</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
